33:18.363 --> 33:23.368 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But these and other renewable
energy efforts
need to be increased, according
to Danish

33:23.401 --> 33:25.269 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
climate scientist Sebastian
Mernild.

33:25.303 --> 33:28.606 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEBASTIAN MERNILD, Climate
Scientist: Regarding
this green development, we can
hardly see

33:28.639 --> 33:34.746 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
any impact so far, because the
amount of CO2
in the atmosphere is increasing
year by year.

33:34.779 --> 33:38.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We are for sure helping the
environment, but
not enough.

33:38.182 --> 33:40.385 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we need to speed up this
green development.

33:40.418 --> 33:44.789 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The European
